President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the U.S. Virgin Islands due to Hurricane Irma. Federal aid will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the territory. The declaration makes Federal funding available to affected individuals in the islands of St. John and St. Thomas. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to help individuals and business owners recover from the disaster. Federal funding is also available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures throughout the territory. William L. Vogel has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional areas may be designated for assistance after the assessments are completed. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can begin applying for assistance tomorrow through online registration or by calling the toll-free numbers provided.